      "id": "11112222-1111-4111-8111-222222222222",
      "name": "Set Decision reenable",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.set",
      "typeVersion": 3.4,
      "position": [
        1400,
        300
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {},
      "id": "22223333-2222-4222-8222-333333333333",
      "name": "No-Op (within threshold)",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.noOp",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1400,
        440
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "={{ JSON.stringify($json) }}",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "=Goal:\nExecute the feature-flag decision from upstream Switch for {{ $json.feature_id }}.\n\nDecision from upstream: {{ $json.decision }} (deactivate | reenable).\nCurrent status (from Get Feature Status node): {{ $json.current_status }}.\nCurrent error_rate: {{ $json.error_rate }}.\n\nAvailable tools (you MUST use them; never fabricate):\n- get_feature_info(feature_id) \u2014 re-reads state\n- set_feature_state(feature_id, state) \u2014 mutates status\n\nEXECUTION RULES (mandatory, no exceptions):\n1. Your FIRST action MUST be a tool call to get_feature_info to confirm current state.\n2. If mutation is needed (per the rules below), you MUST call set_feature_state.\n3. After mutation, you MUST call get_feature_info AGAIN to read the new state.\n4. The \"new_state\" field MUST be the literal object returned by the LAST get_feature_info call.\n5. If you skip any required tool call, your output is INVALID.\n\nMutation rules:\n- decision=\"deactivate\" + current status != \"Disabled\" \u2192 set_feature_state(state=\"Disabled\").\n- decision=\"deactivate\" + current status == \"Disabled\" \u2192 no mutation; action_taken=\"no_op\", reason=\"already_disabled\".\n- decision=\"reenable\" + current status == \"Disabled\" \u2192 set_feature_state(state=\"Enabled\").\n- decision=\"reenable\" + current status != \"Disabled\" \u2192 no mutation; action_taken=\"no_op\", reason=\"already_enabled\".\n\nAlert message (Ukrainian, one line):\n- deactivated: \"\ud83d\udea8 Feature search_v2 \u0434\u0435\u0430\u043a\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0430: error_rate X% \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0449\u0438\u0432 \u043f\u043e\u0440\u0456\u0433 5%.\"\n- reenabled:   \"\u2705 Feature search_v2 \u0432\u0456\u0434\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0430: error_rate X% \u0432\u043f\u0430\u0432 \u043d\u0438\u0436\u0447\u0435 1%.\"\n- no_op:       \"\u2139\ufe0f Feature search_v2 \u2014 \u0431\u0435\u0437 \u0437\u043c\u0456\u043d (error_rate X%, \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0443\u0441 S).\"\n\nOutput (strict JSON):\n{\n  \"action_taken\": \"deactivated\" | \"reenabled\" | \"no_op\" | \"error\",\n  \"previous_state\": <object from the FIRST get_feature_info> | null,\n  \"new_state\": <object from the LAST get_feature_info> | null,\n  \"alert_message\": string,\n  \"error_rate_percent\": number,\n  \"threshold_used\": number,\n  \"reason\": string | null\n}\n\nFORMAT:\n- Return JSON only. First char `{`, last char `}`.\n- DO NOT wrap in markdown code fences.",
          "maxIterations": 6,
          "returnIntermediateSteps": true
        }
      },
      "id": "33334444-3333-4333-8333-444444444444",
      "name": "Monitor Agent",
